com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop

Class QueuePopulatorExcelWithAssociations

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop.QueuePopulatorExcel
        • com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop.QueuePopulatorExcelWithAssociations
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PipelinePopulateQueueEventListener

    public class QueuePopulatorExcelWithAssociations
extends QueuePopulatorExcel
    QueuePopulator class which loads migration source data from an Excel spreadsheet. This class allows for a document and its associations to be on multiple lines in the spreadsheet. To do so, the class requires an association type and association attribute to be injected. The class loads the items as expected except when the value of the injected assocation attribute equals the value of the previous line. In this case, the item is added as a sub-item (of the injected association type) to the most recently created top level item.

      • associationType

        protected java.lang.String associationType
        Injected, required. Name of Association type. Will correspond to one of the types defined in #MigrationNode

      • associationAttr

        protected java.lang.String associationAttr
        Injected, require. Name of attribute to "split" queueItems on. If sequential values of this attribute are the same, the subsequent rows will be added as a sub-queueItem to the most recently created main queueItem.

      • createQueueItem

                               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> extraProperties,
                               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,AttributeDataType> extraPropertiesDataType)
        Excel with associations implementation of loadPropertiesMap. If the queue item to be created has a current association value that is equal to the association value found on the previous node on previousAssociationAttrValue, then this queue item will be added as an association to the previous queue item saved on previousQueueItem. Otherwise, if the associations don't match, a new queue item will be created.
